<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-07-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="424" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d424">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Señor
                                    <persName type="to">Romero</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-07-09"><hi rend="italic">July 9,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 138.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note of the 2d instant, and to inclose herewith,
                            pursuant to existing treaty stipulations between the United States and
                            Mexico, a warrant of surrender of Inez Ruiz, charged with the crimes of
                            murder, arson, robbery, and kidnaping in Mexico, and held for
                            extradition by L. F. Price, United States commissioner for the western
                            district of Texas.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>